    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-01T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-01T19:00:00-05:00" n="765"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d765">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 652.119/2162e</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WJE1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Willard</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-01T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 1, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1752. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_CTL1">Chadbourne</persName>
                    [from War Trade Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 343. We are advised by <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MG1"
                        >McFadden</persName> that he is unable at least for the present to proceed
                    to Spain to negotiate for horses and mules, but that Senator
                        <persName>Hollis</persName> has gone to Madrid as personal representative of
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PGJJ1">General Pershing</persName>.
                    You will please cooperate in the fullest possible manner with Senator
                        <persName>Hollis</persName>, lending him the fullest assistance of your
                    organization and advising us as to any pressure which in your opinion should be
                    exerted or any concession which might be offered to secure the desired
                    result.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
